
# 📘 STRINGS (DETAILED + INTERVIEW LEVEL) 🔥🔥

---

# 🧠 1️⃣ What is String?

## ✅ Definition

A **String** is a sequence of characters.

```java
String name = "Jay";
```

---

## 💡 Important Point

👉 In Java, **String is NOT primitive**
👉 It is a **class (object)**

---

# 🧠 2️⃣ String Immutability (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥🔥)

## ✅ Definition

String is **immutable** → cannot be changed after creation

---

## 🔍 Example

```java
String s = "Hello";
s.concat(" World");

System.out.println(s);
```

👉 Output:

```
Hello
```

👉 Because:

* New object created ("Hello World")
* Old string not changed

---

## 🧠 Memory Concept (INTERVIEW GOLD)

```java
String s1 = "Java";
String s2 = "Java";
```

👉 Both point to **same object** (String Pool)

---

```java
String s3 = new String("Java");
```

👉 New object in heap (different)

---

# 🔥 Interview Questions

👉 Why String is immutable?

* Security
* Performance (String pool)
* Thread safety

---

# 🧱 3️⃣ String Pool (VERY IMPORTANT)

## ✅ Definition

A special memory area in heap where strings are stored

---

## 💡 Example

```java
String a = "Hello";
String b = "Hello";
```

👉 Only **one object created**

---

# 🔥 Interview Trick

```java
String a = "Hello";
String b = new String("Hello");

System.out.println(a == b);       // false
System.out.println(a.equals(b));  // true
```

👉 `==` → reference
👉 `.equals()` → value

